      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "This behavior is intentional. Unconfirmed and failed transactions are supposed to be sorted to the top to signal something went wrong.\n(what is missing, though, is a way to remove them. There are plans to add this in a future version)\n\nAlso date order is unreliable and ambiguous. Bitcoin transaction, in general, have no date field, so what the UI and RPC show is best effort guesswork.\n",
